<section class="content-section">
  <div class="app-container about-layout">
    <div class="panel">
      <span class="eyebrow">Why SynthGain exists</span>
      <h1>A focused marketplace for people who actually care about vintage synthesizers.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        General marketplaces optimise for volume. SynthGain optimises for clarity, trust, and gear that deserves a
        better sales experience than a generic classifieds page.
      </p>
      <p>
        Buyers need meaningful listing detail. Sellers need a place where rarity, condition, and maintenance history
        are understood. SynthGain narrows the marketplace to that niche and makes the presentation feel deliberate.
      </p>
      <div class="button-row">
        <%= link_to "Browse the marketplace", buyers_path, class: "btn btn-primary" %>
        <%= link_to "Create a listing", user_signed_in? ? new_listing_path : new_user_registration_path, class: "btn btn-outline-dark" %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="stack">
      <div class="panel panel--compact">
        <h2>What makes it different</h2>
        <ul class="feature-list">
          <li>Synth-specific seller profiles and listing context.</li>
          <li>Structured metadata for category, condition, and key features.</li>
          <li>Cleaner buyer flow than a generic feed of unrelated music gear.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="panel panel--compact">
        <h2>Built with</h2>
        <p>Ruby on Rails, PostgreSQL, Bootstrap, Webpacker, Devise, Active Storage, Ransack, and Stripe checkout.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
